    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-11T11:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-11T11:36:00-05:00" n="793"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d793">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6086.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-11T10:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1913—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Public opinion, both native and foreign, as far as I can estimate, seems to be
                    overwhelmingly in favor of Díaz.</p>
                <p>I have taken every possible measure for the safety of the American colony, and
                    its members are active and vigilant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
